text: Guanine nucleotide-binding protein subunit alpha-14 is a protein that in humans is encoded by the GNA14 gene.GUANINE NUCLEOTIDE-BINDING PROTEIN, ALPHA-14; GNA14 at OMIM. Retrieved JULY 25, 2019. G14α is a member of the Gq alpha subunit family, and functions as a constituent of a heterotrimeric G protein in cell signal transduction. ==See also== * Gq alpha subunit * Heterotrimeric G protein ==References==
title: GNA14
